WEBVTT

00:00:06.533 --> 00:00:09.900
♪ Carrying a painful past
That can't be erased ♪

00:00:09.900 --> 00:00:13.000
♪ Don't let go of your will
To live ♪

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:15.500
♪ Oh ♪

00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:19.133
♪ Your hand that I held... ♪

00:00:22.166 --> 00:00:25.867
♪ Will we someday lose it? ♪

00:00:25.867 --> 00:00:29.500
♪ I want to protect you
And your smile ♪

00:00:29.500 --> 00:00:32.900
♪ That's slowly disappearing ♪

00:00:32.900 --> 00:00:34.667
♪ Even your resonating voice ♪

00:00:34.667 --> 00:00:38.166
♪ That calls my name
Has dried up ♪

00:00:38.166 --> 00:00:42.266
♪ Sometimes it is erased
By the wind ♪

00:00:44.600 --> 00:00:47.166
♪ I will find you ♪

00:00:47.166 --> 00:00:52.333
♪ You're hurt by incurable pain
And sadness ♪

00:00:52.333 --> 00:00:55.767
♪ Don't say words like
You can't smile anymore ♪

00:00:55.767 --> 00:00:57.433
♪ Or you hate people ♪

00:00:57.433 --> 00:01:01.367
♪ There's a meaning
To everything that happens ♪

00:01:01.367 --> 00:01:03.467
♪ In the unforeseeable future ♪

00:01:03.467 --> 00:01:06.467
♪ Stay the way you are ♪

00:01:06.467 --> 00:01:10.033
♪ There will come a day
When you realize ♪

00:01:10.033 --> 00:01:12.600
♪ Oh ♪

00:01:12.600 --> 00:01:15.834
♪ You're the only... ♪

00:01:15.834 --> 00:01:17.800
♪ Oh ♪

00:01:17.800 --> 00:01:20.967
♪ Someday you'll understand ♪

00:01:26.533 --> 00:01:29.867
[♪♪♪]

00:02:29.333 --> 00:02:30.633
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

00:02:32.300 --> 00:02:35.700
Unh. Damn it.

00:02:35.700 --> 00:02:38.166
This hangover is killing me.

00:02:38.166 --> 00:02:40.967
Dumbass, I drank more
than you, and I feel fine.

00:02:40.967 --> 00:02:43.800
It's your smoking that makes you
feel like crap every morning.

00:02:43.800 --> 00:02:45.834
Unh! Shut up!

00:02:45.834 --> 00:02:48.433
I didn't hear you give me
crap like that yesterday

00:02:48.433 --> 00:02:50.700
after I kicked your ass.
Want some more?

00:02:50.700 --> 00:02:52.400
Yeah? Come on.
Bring it!

00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:54.266
Draw your sword, you
arrogant little punk,

00:02:54.266 --> 00:02:56.767
and I'll polish you off and then
sweep you up with the trash.

00:02:56.767 --> 00:02:57.767
Polish me off?

00:02:57.767 --> 00:02:59.400
Who the hell talks
like that anymore?

00:02:59.400 --> 00:03:02.000
You better get ready
to die, old man.

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:03.000
[GRUNTING]

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:04.800
[WIND BLOWING]

00:03:04.800 --> 00:03:05.834
Hm?

00:03:05.834 --> 00:03:06.834
Huh?

00:03:06.834 --> 00:03:08.800
What the hell kind
of a sound is that?

00:03:11.867 --> 00:03:15.500
BOTH [IN UNISON]:
Aah! Good morning, Captain
Zaraki! What a surprise!

00:03:15.500 --> 00:03:18.300
Thanks for giving us the honor
of sweeping the streets for you!

00:03:18.300 --> 00:03:19.233
Aah!

00:03:19.233 --> 00:03:21.333
[♪♪♪]

00:03:22.533 --> 00:03:24.667
BOTH:
Huh?

00:03:24.667 --> 00:03:28.233
If you two are gonna goof off,
try to be so obvious about it.

00:03:28.233 --> 00:03:30.700
And you'd better get this
street clean enough to eat off,

00:03:30.700 --> 00:03:31.767
or I'll kill you both.

00:03:31.767 --> 00:03:33.033
You heard the man.

00:03:33.033 --> 00:03:35.433
Keep up the good work if
you want to live. Heh-heh-heh.

00:03:36.700 --> 00:03:39.033
Why the hell would
the captain have

00:03:39.033 --> 00:03:41.000
that fool Aramaki
tagging along with him?

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:42.166
Forget that.

00:03:42.166 --> 00:03:44.333
Weren't there two women
riding on Zaraki's back

00:03:44.333 --> 00:03:46.333
instead of just one?

00:03:46.333 --> 00:03:50.567
Well, just which way am I
supposed to go now, woman.

00:03:51.967 --> 00:03:54.734
I think it's probably that--

00:03:54.734 --> 00:03:56.133
No! It's this way!

00:03:56.133 --> 00:03:57.433
That hurt!

00:03:57.433 --> 00:03:58.734
What was that
for, Yachiru?

00:03:58.734 --> 00:04:00.233
That wasn't
very nice.

00:04:00.233 --> 00:04:02.166
Ha-ha-ha. Kenny knows
it's this way, too.

00:04:02.166 --> 00:04:03.100
Don't you Kenny?

00:04:03.100 --> 00:04:04.834
Perhaps we would
be better off

00:04:04.834 --> 00:04:07.133
just listening
to Orihime, Captain.

00:04:07.133 --> 00:04:09.300
After all, the lieutenant
is not exactly known

00:04:09.300 --> 00:04:11.567
for her accurate sense
of direction.

00:04:11.567 --> 00:04:15.233
Perhaps you should shut
up, cueball head. Ptooey.

00:04:15.233 --> 00:04:17.867
Oh, I'm gonna
kill her for that!

00:04:17.867 --> 00:04:20.200
Hey, come on.
Keep your cool, now.

00:04:20.200 --> 00:04:21.433
You have to admit,
Ikkaku,

00:04:21.433 --> 00:04:23.066
you were kind of
asking for that one.

00:04:23.066 --> 00:04:25.033
Enough of all your bickering.

00:04:25.033 --> 00:04:27.433
I'm just gonna go
with my instincts.

00:04:27.433 --> 00:04:29.333
All right!
That's an excellent plan, sir.

00:04:29.333 --> 00:04:31.400
You go, Kenny, and we'll
follow you anywhere.

00:04:31.400 --> 00:04:32.400
You're the best!

00:04:32.400 --> 00:04:34.500
[BIRD CHIRPING]

00:04:36.633 --> 00:04:37.867
URYU:
Huh?

00:04:39.266 --> 00:04:41.667
A little butterfly just
flew into the room.

00:04:41.667 --> 00:04:44.100
Such a fragile thing. Heh.

00:04:44.100 --> 00:04:47.900
Does this mean that it's
spring in the Soul Society.

00:04:47.900 --> 00:04:50.333
Oh, great. Now he's
seeing butterflies

00:04:50.333 --> 00:04:52.467
and talking to himself.

00:04:52.467 --> 00:04:54.066
Why don't you see
if you can catch

00:04:54.066 --> 00:04:56.333
the pretty butterflies, Uryu.

00:04:56.333 --> 00:04:58.333
What? Why would
I do that?

00:04:58.333 --> 00:05:01.033
And where do you get off
calling me by my first name.

00:05:01.033 --> 00:05:03.266
You are nowhere near a close
enough friend for that.

00:05:03.266 --> 00:05:05.200
And if you're gonna
make insulting comments

00:05:05.200 --> 00:05:07.400
about chasing butterflies,
then you never will be.

00:05:07.400 --> 00:05:08.900
Hey, who said I
wanted to be friends

00:05:08.900 --> 00:05:10.667
with an oddball like
you in the first place?

00:05:10.667 --> 00:05:12.967
URYU:
You must have thought
you could be my friend,

00:05:12.967 --> 00:05:14.600
or you never would
have called me that.

00:05:14.600 --> 00:05:17.233
GANJU:
It's part of the Shiba clan
legacy to always reach out

00:05:17.233 --> 00:05:19.266
in friendship, even to those
who don't deserve it.

00:05:19.266 --> 00:05:21.333
URYU:
What kind of
ridiculous legacy is that?

00:05:21.333 --> 00:05:22.333
[GROWLS]
Shh.

00:05:22.333 --> 00:05:23.633
[CROWD CHATTERING]
Huh?

00:05:23.633 --> 00:05:25.600
What?
What's wrong?

00:05:25.600 --> 00:05:27.300
Listen.
Don't you hear that?

00:05:27.300 --> 00:05:28.967
Both: Hm?
[CROWD CHATTERING]

00:05:28.967 --> 00:05:30.834
Yeah, now that
you mention it.

00:05:30.834 --> 00:05:33.500
MAN 1: Aah! What are you doing?
MAN 2: Get out of here!

00:05:33.500 --> 00:05:34.834
MAN 1: Get out of his way.

00:05:34.834 --> 00:05:36.567
[MEN SHOUTING]

00:05:36.567 --> 00:05:38.300
Well, whatever it
is, it does seem

00:05:38.300 --> 00:05:39.934
like it's headed
this way, huh?

00:05:39.934 --> 00:05:41.667
I'm sure it's just
some kind local parade

00:05:41.667 --> 00:05:43.633
or celebration
or something.

00:05:43.633 --> 00:05:46.233
You think so?

00:05:46.233 --> 00:05:48.867
[BOTH SCREAM]
GANJU: What the hell?

00:05:48.867 --> 00:05:51.967
We're done for!
We're all gonna die! Aah!

00:05:53.467 --> 00:05:56.867
Unh. It's you.
But how can this be?

00:05:56.867 --> 00:05:59.166
[♪♪♪]

00:05:59.166 --> 00:06:04.266
Aah! I never wanted
to see you again,

00:06:04.266 --> 00:06:06.834
Captain Kenpachi Zaraki.

00:06:06.834 --> 00:06:08.767
Huh?

00:06:08.767 --> 00:06:10.600
Not you, too.

00:06:10.600 --> 00:06:13.133
I remember your stupid
haircut and your massive ego.

00:06:13.133 --> 00:06:15.867
I wish I could say the same.

00:06:15.867 --> 00:06:18.333
I have a good memory
for the faces I've seen,

00:06:18.333 --> 00:06:20.433
with the exception
of the ugly ones.

00:06:20.433 --> 00:06:22.900
Hm. You don't know what you're
talking about, pretty boy.

00:06:22.900 --> 00:06:24.333
The fact is,
everyone tells me

00:06:24.333 --> 00:06:26.633
that I look cooler than ever
with all these bandages on.

00:06:26.633 --> 00:06:28.233
Besides, how could
you recognize me

00:06:28.233 --> 00:06:29.667
from before with
my face covered?

00:06:29.667 --> 00:06:32.400
Interesting that he didn't
argue about being ugly.

00:06:32.400 --> 00:06:33.567
[FEMALE GROANING]
Hm?

00:06:33.567 --> 00:06:34.934
[♪♪♪]

00:06:38.066 --> 00:06:40.166
Huh? Orihime?
Huh?

00:06:40.166 --> 00:06:42.767
Oh, hey, Uryu, Chad, and Ganju.

00:06:42.767 --> 00:06:45.800
I'm so glad to see
the three of you are all okay.

00:06:45.800 --> 00:06:51.400
Unh! Ow, Yachiru! Stop. Stop!
[LAUGHING]

00:07:04.667 --> 00:07:07.867
MAN:
Byakuya, sir.
It is almost time, master.

00:07:07.867 --> 00:07:09.400
You should leave
for the Sokyoku.

00:07:11.567 --> 00:07:13.033
Very well, then.

00:07:21.633 --> 00:07:24.333
I'm off now, Hisana.

00:07:26.333 --> 00:07:28.667
TETSUZAEMON:
Aah! This is terrible!

00:07:28.667 --> 00:07:31.567
How could I do
such a thing? Aah!

00:07:31.567 --> 00:07:35.500
[GRUNTING]

00:07:35.500 --> 00:07:37.567
A thousand pardons,
my captain.

00:07:37.567 --> 00:07:39.533
Somehow, I fell asleep
sitting on the toilet,

00:07:39.533 --> 00:07:41.166
and I'm late arriving
to assist you.

00:07:41.166 --> 00:07:43.300
Please allow me to kill
myself as punishment.

00:07:43.300 --> 00:07:46.600
KOMAMURA:
Never mind that.
Calm yourself, Tetsuzaemon.

00:07:46.600 --> 00:07:48.367
Everything is fine.

00:07:48.367 --> 00:07:51.734
All the preparations
have been made.

00:07:51.734 --> 00:07:53.667
Uh...huh?

00:07:53.667 --> 00:07:57.533
You needn't take the blame
for everything, Tetsuzaemon.

00:07:57.533 --> 00:07:58.867
Huh?

00:07:58.867 --> 00:08:01.233
Well, thank you
for saying so, sir.

00:08:01.233 --> 00:08:04.967
Don't try to hide it.
You're worried, aren't you?

00:08:04.967 --> 00:08:06.300
[GASPS]

00:08:06.300 --> 00:08:10.266
You think I may yet doubt the
legitimacy of this execution.

00:08:10.266 --> 00:08:13.367
And so you've been making
excuses and arriving late

00:08:13.367 --> 00:08:14.600
to give me more time

00:08:14.600 --> 00:08:18.567
so I can think it through
until I'm convinced.

00:08:18.567 --> 00:08:21.734
Uh, exactly so, sir.

00:08:21.734 --> 00:08:24.333
Do not worry.
I have no doubts.

00:08:24.333 --> 00:08:25.633
[GASPS]

00:08:25.633 --> 00:08:31.133
My loyalty and dedication to
Captain Yamamoto are absolute.

00:08:31.133 --> 00:08:34.166
When I was despised
and made an outcast

00:08:34.166 --> 00:08:35.300
because of my appearance,

00:08:35.300 --> 00:08:38.400
he was the only one
who believed in me.

00:08:38.400 --> 00:08:41.300
Why would I not spend
the whole of my spirit

00:08:41.300 --> 00:08:43.133
to repay that debt to him?

00:08:43.133 --> 00:08:45.600
I have no doubts.

00:08:45.600 --> 00:08:50.266
If he should ask,
I would give my life.

00:08:50.266 --> 00:08:53.467
How about you,
Kaname?

00:08:53.467 --> 00:08:55.166
[♪♪♪]

00:08:55.166 --> 00:08:58.967
For me, the path
ahead is crystal clear.

00:08:58.967 --> 00:09:01.467
The road
the sightless eyes choose

00:09:01.467 --> 00:09:05.100
will always be the one
not dyed red with blood.

00:09:05.100 --> 00:09:10.367
And I believe that you and
I walk the same path, Sajin.

00:09:13.300 --> 00:09:16.233
[MAN CHEWING]

00:09:16.233 --> 00:09:19.600
What an annoyance.
What a pain in the ass.

00:09:19.600 --> 00:09:21.567
As if it wasn't bad
enough with these Ryokas

00:09:21.567 --> 00:09:23.700
sneaking around and then
some kind of murder.

00:09:23.700 --> 00:09:25.900
Now we got captains
and lieutenants

00:09:25.900 --> 00:09:28.900
all arguing about whether the
execution is legit or not.

00:09:28.900 --> 00:09:30.133
What's there to talk about

00:09:30.133 --> 00:09:32.400
when the superiors have made
their final decision?

00:09:32.400 --> 00:09:34.266
Pretty stupid, don't
you think, Captain?

00:09:34.266 --> 00:09:35.300
SUI-FENG:
Idiotic.

00:09:35.300 --> 00:09:36.467
Huh?

00:09:36.467 --> 00:09:39.000
I have no interest in
who's right or wrong.

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:41.734
I am interested
only in the mission

00:09:41.734 --> 00:09:45.467
and in executing my orders
as the captain of Squad 2.

00:09:45.467 --> 00:09:49.000
I kill enemies.
That's all there is.

00:09:50.633 --> 00:09:53.166
Yeah, huh? I guess so.

00:09:53.166 --> 00:09:54.967
SUI-FENG:
You, too, Marechiyo.

00:09:54.967 --> 00:09:58.867
You had best remember
where your loyalty lies.

00:09:58.867 --> 00:10:01.967
If you cross me,
or try to get in my way,

00:10:01.967 --> 00:10:04.567
then you, too, are my enemy.

00:10:04.567 --> 00:10:07.567
[♪♪♪]

00:10:07.567 --> 00:10:12.000
Yeah. Well, I'll be sure
to remember that.

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:13.266
[CRUNCH]

00:10:13.266 --> 00:10:14.934
[MAN HUMMING]

00:10:22.233 --> 00:10:23.734
[WOMAN GRUNTING]

00:10:23.734 --> 00:10:25.367
Here you are,
Captain.

00:10:25.367 --> 00:10:27.233
I've been looking for you
for an hour now.

00:10:28.934 --> 00:10:31.400
What are you doing
just lying there? Get up.

00:10:31.400 --> 00:10:33.567
You've gotta get ready
to go to the Sokyoku.

00:10:33.567 --> 00:10:35.900
Well, I can't
get up just now.

00:10:35.900 --> 00:10:39.900
I seem to be having a little
problem here at the moment.

00:10:39.900 --> 00:10:41.800
Tell me what you
think I should do.

00:10:41.800 --> 00:10:43.233
[♪♪♪]

00:10:43.233 --> 00:10:44.734
Why?
What is it?

00:10:44.734 --> 00:10:48.133
KYORAKU:
Okay. You see, I put
this blade of grass in my mouth,

00:10:48.133 --> 00:10:49.400
thinking it would relax me.

00:10:49.400 --> 00:10:51.767
But I guess it must
be toxic or something,

00:10:51.767 --> 00:10:53.200
because now,
the more I chew it,

00:10:53.200 --> 00:10:56.000
the more I can feel it burning
the inside of my mouth.

00:10:56.000 --> 00:10:57.433
Try
spitting it out!

00:10:59.066 --> 00:11:00.467
Let me ask you,

00:11:00.467 --> 00:11:05.166
Nanao, what do you
think I should do?

00:11:06.700 --> 00:11:09.333
It doesn't matter what I think.
And we both know that.

00:11:11.266 --> 00:11:13.934
Regardless of any
advice I might give you,

00:11:13.934 --> 00:11:15.734
you'll just go
right ahead

00:11:15.734 --> 00:11:17.867
and do what you were
going to do anyway.

00:11:21.467 --> 00:11:23.033
But don't worry about it.

00:11:23.033 --> 00:11:25.533
I'll be sure to walk
several steps behind you

00:11:25.533 --> 00:11:26.934
when we get there.

00:11:26.934 --> 00:11:29.633
That way, I won't get dragged
into whatever trouble you cause.

00:11:31.567 --> 00:11:33.500
That's too bad.

00:11:33.500 --> 00:11:35.233
[GROANS]

00:11:35.233 --> 00:11:37.400
That means
I'll be on my own.

00:11:37.400 --> 00:11:41.233
And old man Yamamoto
will blame it all on me.

00:11:41.233 --> 00:11:43.033
[GASPS]

00:11:49.934 --> 00:11:52.166
[CROWD GASPING]

00:11:56.734 --> 00:11:59.166
ZARAKI:
Another dead end.

00:11:59.166 --> 00:12:01.133
Well,
let me explain.

00:12:01.133 --> 00:12:02.934
You see,
it's not that easy.

00:12:02.934 --> 00:12:04.467
Guiding a big group
through a city

00:12:04.467 --> 00:12:06.367
is really more luck
than it is science.

00:12:06.367 --> 00:12:09.467
ORIHIME:
Sure, you could run
into dead ends 10 or 12 times

00:12:09.467 --> 00:12:10.600
before finding your way.

00:12:10.600 --> 00:12:13.367
I told you we shouldn't
let the lieutenant lead.

00:12:13.367 --> 00:12:15.967
What would you expect to happen
when you follow someone around

00:12:15.967 --> 00:12:17.567
who has no sense of direction?
Huh?

00:12:17.567 --> 00:12:21.133
Aah! Someone get
this creature off me!

00:12:21.133 --> 00:12:23.100
[BOTH GRUNTING]

00:12:24.934 --> 00:12:27.633
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

00:12:28.667 --> 00:12:31.033
Captain?
Yes?

00:12:31.033 --> 00:12:34.266
You should be ashamed
of yourselves, boys,

00:12:34.266 --> 00:12:36.066
sneaking around like that.

00:12:36.066 --> 00:12:38.467
Show yourselves.

00:12:38.467 --> 00:12:41.400
Hiding your spiritual pressure
in order to stalk others

00:12:41.400 --> 00:12:43.433
is no way for a captain to act.

00:12:43.433 --> 00:12:45.467
[♪♪♪]

00:12:45.467 --> 00:12:46.767
[BANG]

00:12:46.767 --> 00:12:50.100
KOMAMURA:
Your arrogance knows
no bounds, Kenpachi,

00:12:50.100 --> 00:12:53.900
to talk that way, given what
you appear to be involved in.

00:12:59.767 --> 00:13:02.200
[ALL GASPING]

00:13:02.200 --> 00:13:05.166
What are you doing
with these Ryoka?

00:13:05.166 --> 00:13:09.166
Did you lose your self-respect
when you were defeated?

00:13:09.166 --> 00:13:14.333
Ugh. Captain Komamura,
Captain Tosen, Lieutenant Iba

00:13:14.333 --> 00:13:16.000
and Lieutenant Hisagi?

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:17.166
Oh, damn.

00:13:17.166 --> 00:13:19.433
Don't get your
panties in a twist.

00:13:19.433 --> 00:13:21.567
We still outnumber
them almost two to one.

00:13:21.567 --> 00:13:24.066
Yeah, but it's not
numbers I'm worried about.

00:13:24.066 --> 00:13:26.266
ZARAKI: Quit whining.
[BOTH GASP]

00:13:26.266 --> 00:13:27.934
Who ever said any
of you are going

00:13:27.934 --> 00:13:29.900
to be in this fight
in the first place?

00:13:29.900 --> 00:13:31.900
[♪♪♪]

00:13:31.900 --> 00:13:36.400
After all, even taking these
guys on four against one

00:13:36.400 --> 00:13:38.934
won't give my blade much
more than a little practice.

00:13:41.066 --> 00:13:43.066
KOMAMURA:
Four to one, you say.

00:13:43.066 --> 00:13:45.266
So, you think
you are good enough

00:13:45.266 --> 00:13:47.800
to fight all of us
by yourself, Kenpachi?

00:13:47.800 --> 00:13:50.133
Though your strength
is well known, Captain,

00:13:50.133 --> 00:13:53.200
it is no match for
your excessive self-confidence,

00:13:53.200 --> 00:13:54.667
as you will soon learn.

00:13:54.667 --> 00:13:56.200
[♪♪♪]

00:13:56.200 --> 00:13:58.467
ZARAKI:
You talk too much, Sajin.

00:14:01.533 --> 00:14:04.700
Just hurry up
and fight already.

00:14:04.700 --> 00:14:08.500
And the four of you had better
attack at the same time.

00:14:08.500 --> 00:14:10.633
If you come at me
from all four sides,

00:14:10.633 --> 00:14:15.700
then one of you might actually
be able to wound me.

00:14:16.400 --> 00:14:17.867
Uh, Captain, sir?

00:14:17.867 --> 00:14:19.734
Um. What about us?

00:14:19.734 --> 00:14:21.233
What'll we do, sir?

00:14:21.233 --> 00:14:23.367
Go! You'll just
get in the way.

00:14:23.367 --> 00:14:25.266
Okay, okay.

00:14:25.266 --> 00:14:27.633
But he didn't have
to be so mean about it.

00:14:27.633 --> 00:14:29.367
Come on. Get
over it, Whiskers.

00:14:29.367 --> 00:14:31.166
Kenny's happy right now.

00:14:31.166 --> 00:14:33.400
Believe me, you don't
want to mess with that.

00:14:33.400 --> 00:14:36.467
MAKIZO:
Don't tell me you've changed
my nickname to Whiskers!

00:14:36.467 --> 00:14:38.567
We're
gonna go now!

00:14:38.567 --> 00:14:40.667
We'll go find Ichigo,
and you catch up later.

00:14:40.667 --> 00:14:41.667
Okay,
Kenny?

00:14:41.667 --> 00:14:43.000
[♪♪♪]

00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:44.667
ZARAKI:
I'll be right there.

00:14:44.667 --> 00:14:49.233
Muscles, Jiggles, Monkey,
Pencil, let's get going!

00:14:49.233 --> 00:14:50.600
Uh,
what did you say?

00:14:50.600 --> 00:14:52.033
[BELL DINGS]
Huh?

00:14:52.033 --> 00:14:54.266
Did I just
get nicknamed Pencil?

00:14:54.266 --> 00:14:56.166
Oh, you'll figure
it out eventually.

00:14:56.166 --> 00:14:57.867
You too, Whiskers.
Run everybody, run!

00:14:57.867 --> 00:14:59.800
MAN 1: Wait for me!
MAN 2: We're coming!

00:14:59.800 --> 00:15:01.834
MAN 1:
I'm not staying here!

00:15:01.834 --> 00:15:04.734
I'll be right there, huh.

00:15:04.734 --> 00:15:08.567
It seems you're deliberately
trying to provoke us now.

00:15:08.567 --> 00:15:10.934
Or do you really believe
you can defeat

00:15:10.934 --> 00:15:12.767
all four of us that easily?

00:15:12.767 --> 00:15:14.000
Either way, it looks like

00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:17.667
you've lost your grasp
on sanity, Kenpachi.

00:15:17.667 --> 00:15:20.000
ZARAKI:
Ha, sanity.

00:15:20.000 --> 00:15:23.133
What would I do with
something as useless as that?

00:15:23.133 --> 00:15:27.033
Lucky for me, I never
had any such thing.

00:15:27.033 --> 00:15:30.033
ORIHIME:
Yachiru, wait a minute!

00:15:30.033 --> 00:15:31.266
Hm?

00:15:31.266 --> 00:15:33.834
Are you sure it's a good
idea to leave your captain?

00:15:33.834 --> 00:15:36.000
He's pretty heavily
outnumbered back there.

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:37.333
Oh, no problem.

00:15:37.333 --> 00:15:40.934
Those guys could never beat
Kenny, even if was 20 to one!

00:15:40.934 --> 00:15:43.266
Yachiru.

00:15:43.266 --> 00:15:45.400
MAKIZO:
This Ryoka girl
sure has some nerve,

00:15:45.400 --> 00:15:48.066
calling the lieutenant
by her first name like that.

00:15:48.066 --> 00:15:50.133
Either that or she's crazy!

00:15:50.133 --> 00:15:52.667
Right, you two? Can you
believe nerve of this girl?

00:15:52.667 --> 00:15:54.033
What do you think, sir?

00:15:54.033 --> 00:15:56.667
Huh? Hey, where did they go?

00:15:56.667 --> 00:15:58.934
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

00:16:01.200 --> 00:16:03.934
Captain, allow me.

00:16:03.934 --> 00:16:07.200
And me. Let the two of us
go first, Captain.

00:16:07.200 --> 00:16:09.166
You idiots.

00:16:09.166 --> 00:16:12.066
I told you I want all four
of you to attack me at once.

00:16:12.066 --> 00:16:14.467
YUMICHIKIA:
You think so little
of us you would send in

00:16:14.467 --> 00:16:15.767
only your lieutenants?
Huh?

00:16:15.767 --> 00:16:18.066
What an insult
to our captain.

00:16:18.066 --> 00:16:20.467
If that's the case, sir, then
the two of us should go first.

00:16:20.467 --> 00:16:23.133
What the-- Why didn't
you two clear out

00:16:23.133 --> 00:16:25.200
along with the others,
like I told you?

00:16:25.200 --> 00:16:26.633
Listen, all four of you.

00:16:26.633 --> 00:16:28.033
You've got a lot
of nerve to think

00:16:28.033 --> 00:16:29.934
your two lousy lieutenants
are good enough

00:16:29.934 --> 00:16:33.133
to take on Squad 11's
Captain Zaraki by themselves.

00:16:33.133 --> 00:16:34.266
In fact, you should be happy

00:16:34.266 --> 00:16:36.133
just to have me
as your opponent.

00:16:36.133 --> 00:16:38.500
Right, Captain?

00:16:38.500 --> 00:16:41.367
Ha. So in other words,
you two clowns

00:16:41.367 --> 00:16:43.133
wanna get in on the fight?

00:16:43.133 --> 00:16:44.433
All right, then. Go.

00:16:44.433 --> 00:16:46.166
I'll
give them over to you.

00:16:46.166 --> 00:16:48.767
But take it somewhere else,
so you don't get in my way.

00:16:48.767 --> 00:16:50.333
Or I'll have to kill
you both myself.

00:16:50.333 --> 00:16:52.400
BOTH [IN UNISON]:
Thank you, sir.

00:16:53.900 --> 00:16:56.266
I can hardly believe
what I'm hearing.

00:16:56.266 --> 00:16:58.800
You guys arguing over
who's going to fight us.

00:16:58.800 --> 00:17:00.800
You certainly have
gotten pretty cocky

00:17:00.800 --> 00:17:03.667
since the last time
I saw you Ikkaku.

00:17:03.667 --> 00:17:06.500
A coward who had to
transfer to another squad

00:17:06.500 --> 00:17:08.400
just because he
couldn't make the grade

00:17:08.400 --> 00:17:09.633
and become a lieutenant in ours

00:17:09.633 --> 00:17:13.166
has no business
lecturing me, Tetsuzaemon.

00:17:13.166 --> 00:17:15.834
You're going to pay
for that, Ikkaku.

00:17:15.834 --> 00:17:18.600
Well, if I do, it won't
be here. Let's get moving.

00:17:18.600 --> 00:17:21.667
I have no desire to be
killed by our captain.

00:17:21.667 --> 00:17:23.400
Yes, let's do it.

00:17:23.400 --> 00:17:26.100
Are you two ready to take
this fight somewhere else?

00:17:26.100 --> 00:17:29.367
It won't matter.
You'll die just the same.

00:17:30.967 --> 00:17:32.066
ZARAKI:
All right, then.

00:17:32.066 --> 00:17:34.033
We can finally get
down to business.

00:17:34.033 --> 00:17:36.934
Of course, your number
has been cut by half.

00:17:36.934 --> 00:17:39.767
This will probably
be no more of a workout

00:17:39.767 --> 00:17:42.166
than my morning exercises.

00:17:42.166 --> 00:17:44.400
And still, you brag.

00:17:44.400 --> 00:17:47.633
I think the time has come
to put an end...

00:17:47.633 --> 00:17:50.533
to your arrogance!

00:17:50.533 --> 00:17:52.767
Here I come!
[GASPS]

00:17:55.867 --> 00:17:57.834
[♪♪♪]

00:18:00.700 --> 00:18:03.633
Now stand back, Sajin.

00:18:05.467 --> 00:18:07.934
I will break all his limbs.

00:18:07.934 --> 00:18:10.400
Suzumushi Nishki.

00:18:12.667 --> 00:18:14.400
Benihiko!

00:18:19.333 --> 00:18:21.533
[♪♪♪]

00:18:36.233 --> 00:18:38.233
It's over.

00:18:38.233 --> 00:18:42.600
Not even Kenpachi Zaraki could
have survived such an attack.

00:18:45.166 --> 00:18:46.967
[ZARAKI LAUGHING]

00:18:53.800 --> 00:18:55.567
That's it?

00:18:55.567 --> 00:18:56.533
That's all you got?

00:18:56.533 --> 00:18:57.967
[♪♪♪]

00:18:57.967 --> 00:18:59.533
[GASPING]

00:18:59.533 --> 00:19:01.467
Impossible.

00:19:01.467 --> 00:19:06.900
Tenken, Benihiko, how
can he still be standing?

00:19:08.166 --> 00:19:10.333
ZARAKI:
Oh, dear.

00:19:13.633 --> 00:19:16.000
Forget what I said before.

00:19:16.000 --> 00:19:19.300
My morning exercise
is tougher than this.

00:19:28.467 --> 00:19:31.000
Well then, I guess
I'll be going.

00:19:32.000 --> 00:19:33.100
ICHIGO:
All right.

00:19:41.900 --> 00:19:43.867
Tell me
the truth, Yoruichi.

00:19:43.867 --> 00:19:46.066
What do you think?

00:19:46.066 --> 00:19:48.367
Do you still think he's
going to be able to do this?

00:19:50.700 --> 00:19:52.934
[♪♪♪]

00:19:52.934 --> 00:19:54.700
Because we're out of time.

00:19:54.700 --> 00:19:57.433
Can he really
reach Bankia today?

00:19:57.433 --> 00:19:58.767
[GASPING]

00:20:07.467 --> 00:20:10.400
Let's go, Ichigo.
One more time now.

00:20:11.100 --> 00:20:12.900
And let me be clear.

00:20:12.900 --> 00:20:14.900
Just because the hour
is drawing near,

00:20:14.900 --> 00:20:17.333
I don't intend
to go easy on you.

00:20:17.333 --> 00:20:19.100
No, of course, you won't.

00:20:19.100 --> 00:20:20.967
And that's because I'm
not gonna give you

00:20:20.967 --> 00:20:22.734
the chance to go easy on me.

00:20:22.734 --> 00:20:25.200
Renji.
Hm?

00:20:25.200 --> 00:20:27.500
Do you remember the first time
when you were a child

00:20:27.500 --> 00:20:29.667
that you stood up
and walked on your own?

00:20:29.667 --> 00:20:31.533
What?
Of course not.

00:20:31.533 --> 00:20:33.734
No one remembers
anything that early.

00:20:33.734 --> 00:20:36.467
If you don't remember doing
it, and yet you did it,

00:20:36.467 --> 00:20:39.233
it means that you weren't
conscious of it at the time.

00:20:39.233 --> 00:20:41.500
So how did you
know how to do it?

00:20:41.500 --> 00:20:43.000
Huh?

00:20:43.000 --> 00:20:46.333
YORUICHI:
The answer is all humans
are born already knowing

00:20:46.333 --> 00:20:50.400
how to stand up, just as birds
are born knowing how to fly,

00:20:50.400 --> 00:20:53.767
and fish are born
already knowing how to swim.

00:20:53.767 --> 00:20:56.200
It's because of what
we call instinct.

00:20:56.200 --> 00:20:58.266
All living creatures
use instinct

00:20:58.266 --> 00:20:59.834
to obtain their
natural powers

00:20:59.834 --> 00:21:01.667
when the time comes
that they need them.

00:21:01.667 --> 00:21:05.567
That's what Ichigo's face
reminds me of.

00:21:05.567 --> 00:21:09.633
I think he knows instinctively,
somewhere deep down inside,

00:21:09.633 --> 00:21:12.433
that he has that power.

00:21:12.433 --> 00:21:16.000
And that is why I still believe

00:21:16.000 --> 00:21:19.533
that he will be the one
to reach Bankai.

00:21:19.533 --> 00:21:21.533
[SHOUTING]

00:21:25.900 --> 00:21:27.700
[PEOPLE SINGING IN JAPANESE
AND ENGLISH]

00:21:27.700 --> 00:21:29.400
♪ Happypeople ♪

00:21:29.400 --> 00:21:32.033
♪ Come on, come on
Come on ♪

00:21:32.033 --> 00:21:34.333
♪ Happypeople ♪

00:21:34.333 --> 00:21:35.633
♪ Here we go ♪

00:21:35.633 --> 00:21:38.767
♪ Everybody stand up ♪

00:21:38.767 --> 00:21:41.967
♪ Everybody's fighting ♪

00:21:44.367 --> 00:21:47.567
♪ But they're actually
Worried ♪

00:21:47.567 --> 00:21:51.767
♪ Keep your head right up ♪

00:21:51.767 --> 00:21:52.867
♪ To the sky ♪

00:21:52.867 --> 00:21:55.133
♪ No matter when ♪
♪ Oh yeah ♪

00:21:55.133 --> 00:21:56.734
♪ No matter where you are ♪

00:21:56.734 --> 00:21:58.867
♪ Oh yeah ♪
♪ Just call me any time ♪

00:21:58.867 --> 00:22:00.033
♪ Oh yeah ♪

00:22:00.033 --> 00:22:02.066
♪ I'll be there for you ♪

00:22:02.066 --> 00:22:06.433
♪ Happypeople's in the house ♪

00:22:06.433 --> 00:22:10.834
♪ With a tough smile ♪

00:22:10.834 --> 00:22:14.900
♪ Happypeople's in the house ♪

00:22:14.900 --> 00:22:18.333
♪ We keep on living ♪

00:22:18.333 --> 00:22:19.467
♪ Well... ♪

00:22:19.467 --> 00:22:23.066
♪ Happypeople ♪
♪ In the house ♪

00:22:23.066 --> 00:22:24.400
♪ All right ♪

00:22:24.400 --> 00:22:26.166
♪ Happypeople ♪

00:22:26.166 --> 00:22:28.500
♪ Mmm, happy ♪

00:22:30.467 --> 00:22:32.500
KON:
Yo, how's everybody doing?

00:22:32.500 --> 00:22:35.266
I'm your idol, Kon, and
this is the last installment

00:22:35.266 --> 00:22:36.533
of the Soul Reaper guidebook.

00:22:36.533 --> 00:22:38.266
Last but not least
is that legendary man.

00:22:38.266 --> 00:22:40.400
By the way, the new Soul
Reaper golden dictionary

00:22:40.400 --> 00:22:42.133
will begin right after
the next episode,

00:22:42.133 --> 00:22:43.967
so be sure to keep
your eyes peeled for it.

00:22:43.967 --> 00:22:45.567
RUKIA:
You mean there's more?

